{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Image Restoration","date":"06-10-2019"},"html":"<p>Let's talk about image restoration. It is a fun topic when you understand the intuition.</p>\n<p>Say you asked a friend to take a picture of you in front of Lake Geneva. But due to his shaky hands, a blurry bad image was produced.</p>\n<p><span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 750px;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 133.33333333333331%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"bad\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/b220e851ddc6e63c975dc92e64ef98d1/a66cd/bad.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/b220e851ddc6e63c975dc92e64ef98d1/4272c/bad.jpg 188w,\n/static/b220e851ddc6e63c975dc92e64ef98d1/1459e/bad.jpg 375w,\n/static/b220e851ddc6e63c975dc92e64ef98d1/a66cd/bad.jpg 750w,\n/static/b220e851ddc6e63c975dc92e64ef98d1/b4133/bad.jpg 1080w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\"\n      />\n  </span></p>\n<p>That's quite sad, since you know the image you wanted should have looked like this:</p>\n<p><span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 750px;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 133.33333333333331%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    ></span>\n    <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;box-shadow:inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"good\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/b6b06bb8424b9a3081b5ea968f3790c2/a66cd/good.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/b6b06bb8424b9a3081b5ea968f3790c2/4272c/good.jpg 188w,\n/static/b6b06bb8424b9a3081b5ea968f3790c2/1459e/good.jpg 375w,\n/static/b6b06bb8424b9a3081b5ea968f3790c2/a66cd/good.jpg 750w,\n/static/b6b06bb8424b9a3081b5ea968f3790c2/b4133/good.jpg 1080w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\"\n      />\n  </span></p>\n<p>Now the question is, is it possible to restore the unwanted effects from the bad image, such that we get the good image?</p>\n<h3>Inverse Filter</h3>\n<h3>Adaptive Filter</h3>"}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"p2"}}